Questions that arise after the accident: Are the stewards in the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance bus is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident of the Student Agency bus near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether the stewards and passengers can travel within the coach during the journey.
"If the law was to be strictly and formally respected, the activity of a steward is contrary to the law on road traffic," said the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the bus's path.
The girl was at that time unfortunately sitting next to the driver, in the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she had two more seats at her disposal.
However, the coach can have an accident or even a sudden brake, also when the steward serves coffee or distributes newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is under its technical data sheet equipped with standing or not.
If this standing equipment is not approved, the passengers shall remain seated.
Student Agency long-distance buses do not have standing places; this was confirmed in Aktuálně.cz by the director of the company Radim Jančura.
"This is a matter that we have dealt with with the ministry and, at first, it prohibits the movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got that the passengers can go to the bathroom during the trip provided they have their own seat," he revealed his position.
The law ignores the steward
"There is no single legal interpretation of the role of steward - no legal requirement deals with this role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement also prohibits the carrier from offering services.
The law on road transport only knows the term "vehicle receiver"; it does not define its rights and duties," added Hanzelka, with more ambiguity.
Josef Pokorný, the director of the Road Vehicle Traffic Department, believes, on the contrary, that the law adequately addresses the problem.
"It all depends on whether the coach has in its approval permission to propose standing places.
It's all in there," he said.
Buses are divided into urban areas, where there are standing places and a limited maximum speed, tolls with standing places and a higher permitted speed and long distance buses without standing places with the highest permitted speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
As on the plane, says an expert.
Jaroslav Hořín, an expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"During regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
There, too, it is not sure when turbulence will occur and the air hostess can hit her head."
"But in the event that the bus would have braked abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as on an urban bus or in a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of the stewards by internal requirements," he says and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not resolved.
Jančura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only coach carrier to offer stewards services.
He hires two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their trade to be a trade at risk.
"However, as soon as I feel that this is a risky job, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper on boarding.
It would also reduce costs," he said.
The safety concern is the reason given by the director of Asiana Alexey Litvine for the absence of stewards in his vehicles, who, in comparison with SA, ensures a very small number of lines.
"We don't have a hostess. We've been opposing it from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end in a fatal accident," he said, a year ago, in Týden.cz.
A great tragedy has come
A young hostess from the region of Plzes, who had been working for the company for two years, died during the accident on the line of Naples.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop band without using a flasher and blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid him by means of a sudden manoeuvre, but he approached him by his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the stewards' rest have been sold.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the driver of the truck.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the judgment of the court, but as regards the financial compensation, it also relies on the culprit.
An amendment to the Act?
Not in sight
An amendment to the Act, which has been being drafted for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could clarify the travel of stewards on board the bus.
"However, it did not reach any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of mobile phones at the wheel," said expert Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of stewards as something that would fundamentally endanger the safety of passengers," concludes spokesman Hanzelka, noting that the control of the safety of coaches is under the authority of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
The hopes of the Düsseldorfois rest on Frankfurt.
The key words were not missing in the letter from the WestLB Steering Committee to the employees of the house.
By a union of the entities of the Düsseldorf financial institute with the Frankfurt Deka-Bank, "the central financial market institution of the Sparkasse financial group" could be formed, according to the letter made public on Monday.
