"Because of the country's debt and the rising trade deficit, the collapse of social security, 'evoking the silence of a cemetery', is only a matter of time," Milinkevich believes.
Unlike the opposition politician, the Russian observers called the elections democratic.
Sergei Lebedev, leader of the mission of the Community of Independent States, told the Russian news agency Ria Novosti: "People do not believe in words, but in acts." In this way, the absence of the opposition is only proof of the maturity of Belarusian voters.
