Waves, currents, tides, these are the new renewable sources on which colossals like Chevron have laid their eyes, and now are trying to get their hands on them.
The possibility of obtaining energy from the movements of the sea has now been studied for a hundred years, and in the 1970s, in conjunction with the first oil crisis, research has intensified.
When the price of oil fell, around 1980, the idea of exploiting marine energy was set aside, but now the environmental authorities and the new increase in oil give a big boost to the sector.
The World Energy Council (WEC) in London estimated in 2007 that 15% of the global electricity requirement could be covered by sea swell systems.
This amount would be twice the amount produced by nuclear power plants.
And besides, there would be currents and tides..
Colossus to attack.
